      "text": " Let  $p \\in \\Delta^{|S|-1}$  be a probability distribution on  $s$  in a round. As the name Markov matrix implies, a distribution in the next round  $p'$  is given by  $p' = Mp$ , where  $M$  is a Markov transition matrix;",
      "line_with_spans": [
        {
          "category_type": "text_span",
          "poly": [
            297.4999999999999,
